Array - array is a Finite, ordered and collection of Homogeneous Data Items.
      - array is used for a variable to store more than one data.

      finite - fix size of data.
      ordered - stored in contigeous memory allocations.
      homogeneous - same type of data, float array consists of only float, int array consists of only int values.

      arr. length - for(i=0; i<arr.length; i++)

      Creation of array -  int arr[] = new int[10];